# Installation

React Router is a separate package. Install it with npm or yarn:

```bash
npm install react-router-dom
```

`react-router-dom` contains the DOM bindings (for web apps).

## BrowserRouter

The main router component is `BrowserRouter`. It uses the HTML5 history API to keep your UI in sync with the URL. You typically wrap your entire app with it.

```jsx
import { BrowserRouter } from 'react-router-dom';

function App() {
  return (
    <BrowserRouter>
      <div>Your app content</div>
    </BrowserRouter>
  );
}
```

